<subSubSection id="2D966540FFA3FFEF46D7FBE996A1FBD1" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="653336CBFFA3FFEF46D7FBE996A1FBD1" blockId="18.[151,1437,1031,1560]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis id="57F8EAD9FFA3FFEF46D7FBE9929AFB99" bold="true" box="[151,433,1031,1056]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Comparative diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A28C4D48FFA3FFEF446DFBE791CCFB99" box="[557,743,1031,1056]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Wroughtonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhejiangensis">
<emphasis id="57F8EAD9FFA3FFEF446DFBE791CCFB99" box="[557,743,1031,1056]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">W. zhejiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="A28C4D48FFA3FFEF4560FBE7905FFB99" box="[800,884,1031,1056]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Wroughtonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="57F8EAD9FFA3FFEF4560FBE7905FFB99" box="[800,884,1031,1056]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">W. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has vein 1r-m of hind wing about as long as vein 1-M, the ventral protuberance of the hind femur wide (narrow in 
<taxonomicName id="A28C4D48FFA3FFEF452AFBC39708FBFC" box="[874,1059,1068,1093]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Wroughtonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhejiangensis">
<emphasis id="57F8EAD9FFA3FFEF452AFBC39708FBFC" box="[874,1059,1068,1093]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">W. zhejiangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the precoxal sulcus shallow and without rugae (distinctly impressed and with rugae) and the hind coxa is reticulate dorsally (sparsely punctulate).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2D966540FFA3FFEF4687FB9A92A8FB34" box="[199,387,1140,1165]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" type="biology_ecology">
